The paper deals with algorithms for finding specific types of patterns (gapped repeats and subrepetitions) in a word, which is a classic problem in string algorithms and data structures. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves analyzing the number of occurrences of these patterns in a word, which could fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper proposes algorithms with time complexity analysis, which could be relevant to cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
